h5.steps to reproduce
# create a Service Desk with different Customer Request Types for (at least) two Issue Types;
# create a Service Desk ticket with Issue type A - it'll have a relevant Customer Request Type assigned to it;
# edit the Issue Type.

*Expected result:* Customer Request Type is updated accordingly with the Issue Type.
*Actual result:* Customer Request Type stays the same.

h3. Steps to reproduce
# Mark a field as required in JIRA's field configuration scheme;
# Create a service desk using a project that uses the field configuration scheme above;
# Try to create an issue;

h3. Current behaviour
You'll see that the required field doesn't have any indication of it;

h3. Expected behaviour
Use the default red asterisk used by JIRA in the Service Desk form.

